  "scientificVerdict": "The original Maeda deposit does not report a measured Reynolds number or complete atmospheric state; the published CFD convention remains an explicit sensitivity input. The c8, c12, and c16 measured-wing feasibility runs remain non-finite and are not quantitative bird results. A host-plumbing audit found that the stationary-sphere validation had incorrectly copied referenceSpeedLattice into the GPU wall velocity instead of the requested wallVelocityLattice. After correction, the true zero-wall, 0.08-flow sphere fails at step 105 for all three published margins, with zero topology events. The 500-step relaxation response is monotonic: failure moves from step 105 to 454 as tauPlus margin rises, and stability begins between margins 0.00999999 and 0.01249999. Selected margins 0.015625, 0.016875, and 0.02 remain finite through 1000 steps, although source-aware force-budget acceptance remains open. At c16 the first negative occurs at step 27, q=10, cell (5,9,12), adjacent to the sphere but pulled from ordinary fluid. All reconstructed incoming populations are positive, all captured stationary-wall corrections are exactly zero, and the one-cell decomposition closes within 7.45e-9. The symmetric TRT increment -0.03093607 creates the negative while the antisymmetric increment is stabilizing. A symmetric limiter keeps the corrected c16 case finite and positive through 500 steps. Its 500-sample ledger closes global population change and attributes the raw gates: open far-field replacement contributes -212.359 mass units, sponge relaxation contributes +152.514, and the limiter contributes only -0.0151, or 4.69e-7 of initial mass. Sponge momentum is 0.125604 N RMS versus 3.34e-7 N RMS from limiting and explains the force residual to 0.287% RMS; boundary load closure is 3.03e-7 relative RMS. Limiter arithmetic and load accounting are therefore cleared. The limiter remains diagnostic-only until a sponge-excluded control volume and source-aware global mass gate pass before the refinement ladder."
